><span class="cn-sprite" id="cn-toggle-15486aae45fc7c" style="background-color: #660066;"></span>\n<span class="fn n"> <span class="given-name">John</span> <span class="family-name">Doe</span> </span>\n</h3><div class="cn-excerpt" id="cn-excerpt-15486aae45fc7c"><p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nunc varius placerat hendrerit. Pellentesque porttitor pharetra felis et feugiat. Aliquam tempor luctus sodales. Quisque porttitor nunc eu nunc tempor non suscipit urna interdum. Nulla enim metus, vestibulum et sagittis a, egestas et mauris. Integer sit amet dolor ante, quis gravida est. Integer quis leo lectus. Vivamus diam tortor,&hellip;</p><span class="cn-show-more" data-uuid="15486aae45fc7c">Read More</span></div><div class="cn-detail cn-hide" id="cn-detail-15486aae45fc7c"><div class="cn-bio" id="cn-bio-15486aae45fc7c">\n<div class="bio"><p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nunc varius placerat hendrerit. Pellentesque porttitor pharetra felis et feugiat. Aliquam tempor luctus sodales. Quisque porttitor nunc eu nunc tempor non suscipit urna interdum. Nulla enim metus, vestibulum et sagittis a, egestas et mauris. Integer sit amet dolor ante, quis gravida est. Integer quis leo lectus. Vivamus diam tortor, suscipit et viverra nec, ultrices vel nulla. Vestibulum feugiat nulla ut ipsum sollicitudin vitae luctus metus euismod. Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Morbi et metus libero, quis mollis  le o.</p>\n</div>\n</div></div></div></div>  <!-- end cn-entry -->\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n<div class="cn-clear" id="cn-list-foot">\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pretty nifty, right? You can use any valid CSS color to match the color scheme of your theme.</p>\n<p>Here are a couple sample shortcodes to show you how:</p>\n\n<div class="wp_syntax"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre class="css" style="font-family:monospace;"><span style="color: #808080; font-style: italic;">/*\n * Change the color to red:\n */</span>\n<span style="color: #00AA00;">&#91;</span>connections template<span style="color: #00AA00;">=</span><span style="color: #ff0000;">''excerpt''</span> <span style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold;">color</span><span style="color: #00AA00;">=</span><span style="color: #ff0000;">''red''</span><span style="color: #00AA00;">&#93;</span>\n&nbsp;\n<span style="color: #808080; font-style: italic;">/*\n * Change the color to plum:\n */</span>\n<span style="color: #00AA00;">&#91;</span>connections template<span style="color: #00AA00;">=</span><span style="color: #ff0000;">''excerpt''</span> <span style="color: #000000; font-weight: bold;">color</span><span style="color: #00AA00;">=</span><span style="color: #ff0000;">''#660066''</span><span style="color: #00AA00;">&#93;</span></pre></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<div class="note"><h4 class="note_title">Important</h4><div class="note_content">Excerpt 2.0 takes advantage of the new and improved template system introduced in version 0.7.6 of Connections. Please read the following installation instructions.</p>\n<p>If you are upgrading from an older version of Excerpt you must go to the Connections : Templates admin page and delete the older version before installing the new version.</p>\n<p>To install the new version, please install it as you would any plugin, please do not use the template installer found on the Connections : Templates admin page. The template installer will only remain in place until all templates have been updated to use the new templating system. After which it will be removed completely.</p>\n<p>After you install Excerpt, as a plugin, activate it as a plugin.</p>\n<p>Finally, after Excerpt has been activated, it will show up on the Connections : Templates admin page and be available for use.</div></div>\n<div class="clearboth"></div>\n<div class="one_third"></div> <div class="one_third"></div> <div class="one_third last">		<!--dynamic-cached-content-->\n		<f